reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 8, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I love it! The price is ridiculously great for it’s quality. The brown switches sound nice, & the build quality is a lot better than I expected. This is a solid, heavy keyboard with a small form factor. The thick USB-C to USB-A cable is a plus, & the lighting (although limited to one color) is fantastic. It’s bright & it looks good. The build quality is enough to justify this purchase alone. This thing feels better than some other $100+ keyboards I’ve owned in the past. The only gripe I have with it is the actual font of the keycaps - but I can easily switch the key caps out in the future. The media keys & the Windows lock button are also an added bonus. I am very impressed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great keyboard to get you in the door.
reviews.reviewText: Not much to say.It's a really nice small form keyboard. It uses off brand switches that mimic cherry.It's a really good way to help introduce someone to a mechanical keyboard.I've had very little issues with the keyboard itself. Periodically the D key will give me some trouble. Aside from that the keys feel very smooth. They are crisp and easy to type on. The function keys are really nice. They all work as expected.The lighting is very nice. You can switch between a handful of different patterns. Just know that you are stuck with blue.I wouldn't use this for gaming. (Since the D key gives me trouble periodically. Put it to your imagination) But, for working in the office its a really great keyboard. I am well happy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Budget KB
reviews.reviewText: So I wasn’t expecting much, just wanted an inexpensive keyboard to use with my Xbox, but I was shocked to see how well this board was made. You can’t find a better keyboard for the price. Easily could be sold for double the price. My only concern is the key caps shown have limited printing on them, while the subtle, the actual key caps have extra printing on them for the light controls.
